The paper deals with secure multiparty computation (MPC) for network security and monitoring, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The paper also involves optimization of computation and communication cost, which can be related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed protocols, which can be related to machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves computation of feature entropy.
